         <abstract>
            <p>An asymptotic expansion is obtained, as $\lambda \rightarrow +\infty$, for the integral $$I(\lambda) = \int^{\pi/2}_0 J^2_\nu(\lambda \cos \theta)d\theta,$$ where $J_\nu(t)$ is the Bessel function of the first kind and $\nu &gt; -\frac{1}{2}$. This integral arises in studies of crystallography and diffraction theory. We show in particular that $I(\lambda) \sim \ln \lambda/\lambda\pi$.</p>
          </abstract>
